# Backend and Security Rules
- Apply Laravel 12 and PHP 8.4 standards. Use strict typing for all files.
- Secure all API routes using Laravel Sanctum.
- Manage Google OAuth logins using Laravel Socialite.
- Use PascalCase for classes, camelCase for methods, and snake_case for database columns.
- Keep controllers thin. Move all business logic into Service classes.
- Keep code comments minimal and only explain complex logic.
- Always recommend the best libraries for new features.